Subject: UBERON:0000066
Value: The stage of development at which the animal is fully formed, including immaturity and maturity. Includes both sexually immature stage, and adult stage.

Subject: UBERON:0000328
Value: We model the digestive tract as consisting of two parts: the wall and the lumen.

Subject: UBERON:0001555
Value: FMA also has a term 'gastrointestinal tract', but this includes the liver.

Subject: BSPO:0000096
Value: x anterior_to y iff x is further along the antero-posterior axis than y, towards the head. An antero-posterior axis is an axis that bisects an organism from head end to opposite end of body or tail: bearer

Subject: BSPO:0000098
Value: x dorsal_to y iff x is further along the dorso-ventral axis than y, towards the back. A dorso-ventral axis is an axis that bisects an organism from back (e.g. spinal column) to front (e.g. belly).

Subject: BSPO:0000102
Value: x ventral_to y iff x is further along the dorso-ventral axis than y, towards the front. A dorso-ventral axis is an axis that bisects an organism from back (e.g. spinal column) to front (e.g. belly).

Subject: RO:0002219
Value: x surrounded_by y iff: x is adjacent to y and for every region r adjacent to x, r overlaps y

Subject: RO:0002220
Value: x adjacent_to y iff: x and y share a boundary

Subject: RO:0002256
Value: t1 developmentally_induced_by t2 if there is a process of organ induction (GO:0001759) with t1 and t2 as interacting participants. t2 causes t1 to change its fate from a precursor tissue type T to T', where T' develops_from T.

Subject: RO:0002387
Value: x has the potential to develop into y iff x develops into y or if x is capable of developing into y

Subject: RO:0002473
Value: x composed_primarily_of y iff: more than half of the mass of x is made from parts of y

Subject: UBERON:0000092
Value: stage succeeding embryo, including mature structure

Subject: UBERON:0001009
Value: organ system that passes nutrients (such as amino acids and electrolytes), gases, hormones, blood cells, etc. to and from cells in the body to help fight diseases and help stabilize body temperature and pH to maintain homeostasis[WP].

Subject: UBERON:0001235
Value: the thick outer layer of the adrenal gland that produces and secretes steroid hormones such as corticosterone, estrone and aldosterone

Subject: UBERON:0002530
Value: an organ that functions as a secretory or excretory organ

Subject: UBERON:0003887
Value: the part of the coelom in the embryo between the somatopleuric and splanchnopleuric mesoderm; the principal body cavities of the trunk (thoracic, abdominal, and pelvic) arise from this embryonic part of the coelom

Subject: UBERON:0010133
Value: any of the organized aggregations of cells that function as secretory or excretory organs and that release hormones in response to neural stimuli

Subject: UBERON:0034878
Value: the area of axial mesoderm that develops into the prechordal plate

Subject: obo:uberon/core#conduit_for
Value: x is a conduit for y iff y passes through the lumen of x.
